nina_b:
  name: Dr Nina Bacos
  email: nbacos@gmail.com
  url: https://www.wild-fires.org/nina-bacos
  bio: Bacos has a BfA and MFA from HFF (now Valand Academy) Göteborg University. She earned her PhD at Glasgow School of Art 2013 and is the founder of the monthly event TalkSeePhotography at the Centre for Contemporary Art in Glasgow. 
  
melanie_r:
  name: Melanie Letoré
  email: 
  url: http://photodialogues.net/melanie-letore
  bio: Melanie Letoré holds a BA (Hons) in Fine Art Photography from the Glasgow School of Art and a Foundation Diploma in Art and Design from Central Saint Martins. She has exhibited nationally and internationally for Futureproof, The Skinny Showcase and Pingyao International Photography Festival, and as part of Wildfires, a photography network for women in Scotland. 

jolanta_d:
  name: Jolanta Dolewska
  email:
  url: http://www.jolantadolewska.com/
  bio: Jolanta Dolewska (MA RCA) is a Glasgow-based artist who works predominantly with photography. She has exhibited in the UK and Northern Ireland and internationally in Italy, Switzerland and South Korea and has been awarded Constance Fairness Foundation Prize, The Photographers' Gallery Award, and was shortlisted for Source-Cord Prize and RSA Morton Award. Dolewska's work has been published in Uncertain States, The Drouth, and Source Photographic Review.

john_f:
  name: John Farrell
  bio: John Farrell is artist and writer based in Glasgow, Scotland. He is a graduate of Glasgow School of Art’s Fine Art Photography department.Working primarily with photography, he has exhibited internationally and throughout Scotland. His critical writing has been published in a number of books and journals, including NOTES and the SSHoP journal Studies in Photography.
  url: www.johnfarrellphotos.com

frances_s:
  name: Frances Scott
  url: https://www.grafik.net/category/talent/frances-scott
  bio: Frances Scott is a photographer and designer from the Orkney Islands. She studied Communication Design at the Glasgow School of Art and has since returned to work at the school as an assistant photography technician. 
  twitter: https://twitter.com/FrancesScott
  
stewart_s:
  name: Stewart Shaw
  bio: Stewart Shaw has enjoyed viewing and making photographs for over fifty years. A finance professional, he has used his experience to assist local photographic initiatives such as the creation of Street Level Photoworks (via Glasgow Photography Group), the networking group Scottish Photographers, and now NOTES Photographic Journal.

